Giving to Immaculata University supports the students, programs, and campus that are the very heart of IU.
Your gifts make both immediate and long-lasting impacts in the following ways:
More than 80% of current Immaculata students receive some form of financial assistance. Your generosity allows Immaculata to offer assistance to ensure IU is accessible to all its students.
Giving to Immaculata provides the ability for the University to quickly respond to emerging opportunities and immediate needs
Supporting Immaculata enhances life on campus, by providing funding for programs that celebrate and advance the Immaculata student experience

We invite you to visit our beautiful campus to experience for yourself the friendly and knowledgeable staff and faculty who can help you determine which program may be the best fit for you. Our financial aid experts excel at explaining how paying for college can be easier than you think, and our admissions staff will guide you through a tour of campus and point out the facts that make Immaculata University an excellent opportunity.

The College of Undergraduate Studies provides many options for students to visit campus throughout the year. Open houses, Information Sessions, and a variety of other events are available. Our daily campus tours are offered Monday through Friday at 10 a.m., 11 a.m., 1 p.m., and 2 p.m. as well as select Saturdays.

On select Tuesdays, Immaculata offers our Transfer Tuesdays from 3 to 6 p.m. During this time, you can meet one-on-one with a counselor who can answer your questions about transferring to Immaculata and will provide you with an unofficial transcript review.
Looking to sit in on classes and get a glimpse of life as a Mighty Mac? Schedule a Shadow Day by clicking on the request form below.
Join us for an Information Session on January 25th and Experience Immaculata University for yourself!

The Information Session will take place on January 25th at 9:00 a.m. At our January Admissions Information Session, a counselor from our admissions office will give an overview of Immaculata University’s academics, campus life, athletics, the admission process, and how to apply for financial aid. The session will provide time for questions and answers and a student-guided tour.

Registration opens at 8:45 am in the Green Room and the program begins at 9:00 am. A continental breakfast will be provided. Attending an Information Session is a great opportunity for you to take an initial look at Immaculata University. Register today!
This is Immaculata. A place where all are truly welcome. A campus that reflects the beauty and charism of its founders. A place where you will be encouraged to discover your fullest self.
If you are an adult looking for flexibility in completing your undergraduate degree, attend an adult undergraduate open house hosted by the College of Adult Professional Studies.

If you are interested in a graduate program, come to an open house hosted by the College of Graduate Studies where you will have a chance to talk with professors and explore academic and research opportunities. Open houses are held four times per year. In addition, students wishing to pursue an M.B.A., can attend online information sessions held throughout the year. For information or to register, visit www.desales.edu/mba and click on “Attend an Info Session.”
